# Agent builds and tests

SwiftPM wraps manifest parsing and compiler subprocesses in macOS `sandbox-exec`, which fails inside Cursor's agent sandbox.

- Use `make agent-test` to verify changes (not `make test`).
- Use `make agent-build` for a release build (not `make build`).
- `make agent-check` runs both.

These Makefile targets pass `--disable-sandbox` to SwiftPM. Do not use `required_permissions: ["all"]` just to run the normal `make test` / `make build` targets.

Humans working outside the agent sandbox should use `make test` and `make build` (SwiftPM sandbox stays enabled for faster, safer local builds).
